  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 375°f.",
    "in a large bowl, combine the pumpkin, onion, garlic, ginger, sherry vinegar, fish sauce, sugar, salt, and black pepper.",
    "mix well to combine.",
    "transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "drizzle the coconut oil over the top and toss to coat.",
    "sprinkle the kaffir lime leaves and dehydrated mushrooms over the top.",
    "cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 30 minutes.",
    "remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 20-25 minutes, or until the top is lightly browned and the pumpkin is tender.",
    "remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving."
  ],
